FBIS4-16224 "drsov072_a_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Russia Rejects `Junior Partner' Status Russia Rejects `Junior Partner' Status LD1304114694 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0830 GMT 13 Apr 94 LD1304114694 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] Russia will never reconcile itself to the role of junior partner who is informed after the event about such important decisions as the use of armed forces in the Bosnia settlement, Grigoriy Karasin, director of the Russian Federation Foreign Ministry's Information and Press Department, stated today at a briefing. Naturally, we will draw the appropriate conclusions from what happened on 10 and 11 April near Gorazde, he stated.
